@startuml transaction_logs_schema
title transaction_logs — Table Schema

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam classAttributeFontSize 12

skinparam class {
  BackgroundColor #FAFAFA
  BorderColor #444444
  HeaderBackgroundColor #E8E8E8
  FontStyle bold
}

class transaction_logs <<(T,#4488CC) table>> {
  .. **Primary Key** ..
  🔑 log_id : String (PK)\nUUID hex
  .. **Tracing (optional)** ..
  correlation_id : String [nullable]
  .. **When / who / where** ..
  created_at : DateTime(tz) [NOT NULL]
  account_number : String [nullable]
  channel : String [NOT NULL]\ndefault ATM_WEB
  .. **HTTP context** ..
  http_method : String [NOT NULL]
  endpoint : String [NOT NULL]
  idempotency_key : String [nullable]
  .. **Payloads (sanitized)** ..
  request_body : JSONB [nullable]
  response_status_code : Integer [NOT NULL]
  response_body : JSONB [nullable]
  .. **Outcome** ..
  outcome : String [NOT NULL]\nsuccess | error | cached
  duration_ms : Integer [nullable]
  error_message : String [nullable]
}

note right of transaction_logs
  **Append-only**
  Rows are INSERTed only;
  never UPDATE or DELETE.

  **Requires** MIDDLEWARE_DB_URL
  If DB disabled → log_event is a no-op.

  **Secrets redacted** before insert
  (pin, jwt, session token, etc.)
end note

note bottom of transaction_logs
  **Not a ledger** — Core Banking owns transactions.
  This table records what the **middleware**
  saw on each /atm/* HTTP call for audit and ops.

  **correlation_id** column exists for future
  cross-service tracing; not populated yet.
end note

@enduml
